## 2. Site structure: gifting is the homepage story

**Recommendation:** Homepage = **gifting**. Full promo capabilities live under **Solutions** (or **Capabilities**), not as the main headline.

```text
Home                    → Gifting-first: problem, process, proof, CTA
Corporate Gifting       → Deep dive: occasions, packages, timeline
How It Works            → Consultation → curate → produce → deliver
Industries              → Construction | Legal & Finance | Tech & Science | …
Solutions               → Embroidery, screen print, in-house production
Case Studies / Gallery  → Real packages (anonymized if needed)
About                   → Story, Michigan roots, rebrand note
Start a Project / Contact → One strong CTA everywhere
```

**Why not only a sublink for gifting?** If gifting is the niche, **Google and humans should land on gifting first**. Solutions supports trust (“we’re not just resellers”). Construction visitors still find you via Industries + case studies.

**Primary CTA language** (speaks to your audience — marketing coordinators, 30–60, mostly women):

- “Plan a gifting program”
- “Book a curation call”
- “Get a sample package idea”

Avoid “Get a quote” on the hero — that sounds like commodity promo. Use quote language on Solutions or secondary buttons.

