## 3. Who you’re talking to (and what they need to hear)

**Primary persona:** Corporate marketing / HR / ops coordinator — often **women 30–60**, juggling events, employee appreciation, client thank-yous, trade shows, and leadership asking “can we do something nice?”

| Industry | Gifting angle |
|----------|----------------|
| **Construction** | Safety milestones, crew appreciation, superintendent gifts, project close-out — durable, practical, premium |
| **Legal / financial / insurance** | Client retention, referral thank-yous, onboarding — understated, quality, no loud logos |
| **Tech / science (Detroit growth)** | Recruitment, lab culture, conference gifts — “not generic startup swag” |
| **General corporate** | Holiday programs, work anniversaries, welcome kits |

**Local SEO:** “Corporate gifting Detroit,” “Michigan embroidered gifts,” “curated employee appreciation packages Michigan” — one page per major theme, not keyword stuffing.

**Trust blocks they expect on a world-class site:**

- Process in 4 steps (with timelines)
- “What’s included” (curation, art, production, packaging, ship-to-multiple-addresses)
- Photos of **real packages**, not stock polo shirts
- “In-house production” — short, visual
- Social proof: logos, short quotes, “programs we’ve run”

